div.h2: Process State Machine All States and Legal Transitions

p.em: Single-core invariant: exactly one process in RUNNING at any instant

tr.td: Must pass through READY; scheduler only picks READY processes
No resurrection; dead PCBs are unlinked and freed
Only one RUNNING at a time on single-core

div.p: Single-Core Invariant current_process pointer always equals the sole RUNNING process. scheduler_tick() runs inside IRQ0 gate (IF=0): no concurrent modification of state machine or process_list_head circular list during transitions.
Invariant: In run queue. Eligible for scheduling. state == PROCESS_READY
Invariant: Exactly ONE process here at any time. state == PROCESS_RUNNING CR3 = this process's PD TSS.ESP0 = kernel_stack_top
Invariant: NOT in run queue. Waiting for external event (keyboard char, sleep timer). state == PROCESS_BLOCKED M4: reserved unused
Invariant: sys_exit called. Unlinked from circular list. Slot recyclable via kfree. state == PROCESS_DEAD
